sed%20in%20Peru.%20He%20was%20hired%20in%202022%2C%20and%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20he%20did%20his%20job%20very%20well.%20But%20then%2C%20I%20started%20to%20receive%20complaints%20from%20clients%20about%20missed%20assignments%20and%20deadlines.%20He%20had%20also%20become%20quite%20unresponsive.%20These%20complaints%20from%20clients%20started%20to%20become%20somewhat%20regular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20this%20employee%20started%20refusing%20certain%20shifts%20he%20usually%20worked%2C%20I%20became%20suspicious.%20I%20had%20a%20feeling%20that%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-multiple-remote-jobs-dont-feel-guilty-overemployed-secret-jobs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoing%20something%20on%20the%20side%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20because%20there%20was%20no%20proof%2C%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20jump%20to%20any%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20instead%2C%20I%20had%20one-on-one%20meetings%20with%20him%20to%20discuss%20his%20job%20performance.%20When%20the%20same%20issues%20continued%2C%20I%20told%20him%20that%20if%20things%20didn't%20change%2C%20I'd%20have%20to%20let%20him%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20showed%20some%20signs%20of%20improvement%2C%20his%20overall%20performance%20didn't%20change%20much.%20This%20put%20a%20significant%20burden%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20team%2C%20who%20had%20to%20cover%20his%20shifts%20and%20deal%20with%20missed%20deadlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d25a224f-ab46-474f-834b-e5a536a52010%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20I%20ultimately%20caught%20him%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20unrelated%20to%20this%20particular%20employee%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emy%20company%20rolled%20out%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-bosses-use-employee-tracking-software-for-remote-workers-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etime-tracking%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20DeskTime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20long-term%20goal%20is%20to%20introduce%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-could-be-here-sooner-than-you-think-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour-day%20workweek%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20my%20company%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20the%20first%20step%20in%20this%20process%20would%20be%20understanding%20how%20my%20employees%20spend%20their%20time%20and%20what%20could%20be%20optimized%20to%20boost%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20our%20entire%20team%20of%20full-time%20employees%20and%20freelance%20contractors%20started%20using%20DeskTime.%20They%20each%20had%20to%20install%20the%20app%20on%20their%20computers%2C%20so%20everyone%20was%20well%20aware%20that%20this%20was%20being%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20I%20looked%20through%20the%20tracking%20data%20of%20the%20struggling%20employee%20and%20noticed%20there%20was%20another%20company's%20name%20%E2%80%94%20a%20US%20business%20%E2%80%94%20that%20regularly%20appeared%20in%20the%20data.%20It%20became%20clear%20to%20me%20that%20this%20employee%20had%20worked%20on%20some%20other%20company's%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20fired%20them%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DeskTime%20data%20showed%20that%20the%20employee%20was%20using%20software%20during%20the%20workday%20that%20was%20unrelated%20to%20his%20job%20tasks.%20It%20also%20included%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-companies-spy-on-employees-bossware-jpmorgan-amazon-monitor-rto-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreenshot%20feature%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20captured%20his%20computer%20screen%20%E2%80%94%20and%20showed%20him%20working%20on%20a%20platform%20where%20the%20other%20company's%20name%20was%20visible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20DeskTime%20data%2C%20I%20estimate%20that%20he%20had%20spent%20close%20to%20half%20of%20his%20work%20time%20working%20for%20this%20other%20company.%20It%20seems%20that%20he%20forgot%20about%20the%20tracking%20software%20since%20once%20it's%20downloaded%2C%20it%20doesn't%20require%20any%20manual%20switching%20on%20and%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20honest%2C%20all%20the%20other%20signs%20%E2%80%94%20missed%20deadlines%2C%20lack%20of%20flexibility%2C%20and%20unresponsiveness%20at%20certain%20times%20%E2%80%94%20had%20already%20made%20me%20quite%20certain%20that%20he%20was%20doing%20something%20else%20during%20working%20hours.%20I%20would%20have%20probably%20fired%20him%20anyway%2C%20but%20the%20tracked%20data%20was%20the%20missing%20hard%20proof.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20he%20was%20working%20for%20the%20other%20company%20full%20time%20because%20soon%20after%20I%20fired%20him%2C%20he%20updated%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile%20to%20reflect%20that%20he%20was%20working%20full%20time%20at%20the%20other%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8efd0a6-5332-4769-9f3c-4c8c5cafa86c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20I%20think%20overemployment%20is%20unethical%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20some%20people%20may%20judge%20me%2C%20but%20I%20really%20don't%20support%20the%20trend%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-jobs-tech-full-time-bosses-work-savings-advice-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoveremployment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20think%20it's%20unethical%20and%20just%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20of%20all%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20team%20who%20have%20to%20cover%20up%20for%20someone%20else's%20low%20performance.%20This%20is%20why%20keeping%20this%20employee%20of%20mine%20in%20the%20company%20wasn't%20an%20option.%20He%20wasn't%20fair%20and%20respectful%20to%20the%20team%2C%20and%20that's%20something%20I%20can't%20tolerate%20%E2%80%94%20his%20actions%20were%20just%20selfish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20I%20don't%20believe%20a%20person%20can%20productively%20do%20two%20jobs%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20even%20if%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-chatgpt-at-work-job-save-time-ai-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20other%20tools.%20Their%20attention%20will%20be%20scattered%2C%20so%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20work%20will%20suffer.%20As%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20I%20have%20to%20think%20about%20my%20business%20and%20clients%20first.%20I%20can't%20afford%20to%20lose%20clients%20because%20someone%20wants%20to%20make%20extra%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20don't%20mind%20people%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-recommendations-jobs-to-try-this-year-concerts-surveys-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eside%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20earn%20extra%20income.%20But%20this%20should%20be%20something%20they%20do%20on%20their%20own%20time%20and%20that%20doesn't%20affect%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20day%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20working%20multiple%20remote%20jobs%20at%20the%20same%20time%20and%20willing%20to%20provide%20details%20about%20your%20pay%20and%20schedule%3F%20Has%20a%20coworker%20or%20employee%20of%20yours%20done%20so%3F%20If%20so%2C%20reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgot-caught-working-two-remote-jobs-fired-unethical-overemployment-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718100181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6667433eed9a404d829c2f68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgot-caught-working-two-remote-jobs-fired-unethical-overemployment-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20CEO%20who%20caught%20an%20employee%20secretly%20working%20a%20second%20job%20shares%20why%20he%20decided%20to%20fire