surely%20summer%20days%20at%20the%20camp.%20They'll%20make%20crafts%2C%20play%20games%2C%20go%20on%20hikes%2C%20enjoy%20daily%20swimming%20lessons%20(they're%20excellent%20swimmers%20now)%2C%20and%20reunite%20with%20camp%20friends.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e471a37a-23bc-4567-8289-ec4429886870%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20kids%20sleep%20so%20much%20better%20at%20camp%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20unexpected%20bonuses%20of%20summer%20camp%20life%20is%20our%20sleep%20habits.%20Our%20kids%20have%20always%20been%20notoriously%20bad%20sleepers%2C%20but%20at%20the%20cabin%2C%20everyone%20sleeps%20like%20a%20rock%20for%20the%20entire%20night.%20The%20combination%20of%20fresh%20air%20and%20active%20days%20seems%20to%20make%20everyone%20feel%20safe%20and%20warm%20in%20their%20respective%20beds.%20Every%20morning%2C%20I%20wake%20up%20refreshed%2C%20clear-headed%2C%20and%20ready%20to%20tackle%20the%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20never%20thought%20I'd%20be%20in%20my%20mid-30s%20living%20at%20a%20children's%20camp.%20Some%20days%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20this%20lifestyle%20is%20much%20more%20suited%20to%20a%20younger%20person%20who%20doesn't%20have%20the%20commitment%20and%20responsibilities%20that%20we%20do%2C%20but%20most%20days%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20a%20dream%20come%20true.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20a%20simplicity%20about%20living%20in%20a%20small%20shared%20space.%20In%20the%20summertime%2C%20I'm%20not%20thinking%20about%20a%20Pinterest-perfect%20kitchen%20(because%20I%20don't%20even%20have%20one)%3B%20when%20the%20floor%20becomes%20covered%20in%20beach%20sand%2C%20it%20doesn't%20bother%20me%2C%20and%20I%20have%20a%20very%20small%20space%20that%20can%20be%20quickly%20tidied%20and%20cleaned.%20Besides%2C%20most%20of%20our%20day%20is%20spent%20outside%20under%20the%20clear%20blue%20sky%20or%20in%20other%2C%20larger%20buildings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20camp%2C%20I've%20found%20a%20closeness%20with%20my%20family%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20before.%20But%20I've%20also%20found%20community%20with%20others.%20When%20we're%20short%20on%20kitchen%20staff%2C%20I'm%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20fill%20the%20space%2C%20chopping%20a%20heaping%20pile%20of%20carrots%20for%20chili%20or%20flipping%20burgers%20on%20the%20barbeque.%20I'll%20gladly%20jump%20into%20the%20lake%20on%20a%20hot%20summer%20day%20with%20my%20girls%20or%20play%20a%20game%20of%20beach%20volleyball.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20go%20to%20bed%20at%20night%2C%20my%20pillow%20smells%20like%20a%20campfire%2C%20sunscreen%2C%20and%20sweat%20%E2%80%94%20all%20signs%20of%20a%20perfect%20day%20at%20summer%20camp.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EBrianna%20Bell%20is%20a%20Canadian%20freelance%20journalist%20with%20work%20published%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20The%20Guardian%2C%20The%20Globe%20%26amp%3B%20Mail%2C%20and%20more.%20Brianna%20is%20currently%20working%20on%20her%20memoir.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-lives-summer-camp-kids-fewer-logistics-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718099941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66633094cc442a2f676f283a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-lives-summer-camp-kids-fewer-logistics-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20family%20of%20five%20moves%20to%20a%20summer%20camp%20all%20summer%20where%20my%20husband%20works.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20350-square-foot%20cabin%20with%20no%20kitchen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Brianna%20Bell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-lives-summer-camp-kids-fewer-logistics-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gen%20Xers%20and%20boomers%20are%20giving%20up%20on%20hybrid%20work%3A%20They're%20either%20all%20in%20or%20out%20on%20the%20office%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20sitting%20in%20office%20drinking%20coffee.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66391ecdb8f515beaf11eda3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOver%20two-thirds%20of%20workers%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2050-64%20are%20working%20fully%20on-site.%3Cp%3EThomas%20M.%20Barwick%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWorkers%20aged%2050-64%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20fully%20on-site%20or%20work%20from%20home%20full%20time%2C%20new%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWorkers%20in%20that%20age%20group%20are%20least%20likely%20to%20work%20hybrid%2C%20compared%20to%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20workers%20aged%2020-29.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESupercommuting%20has%20increased%20by%2032%25%20post-pandemic%2C%20with%20older%20workers%20divided%20on%20work%20preferences.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20older%20workers%20aren't%20the%20type%20to%20spend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-outfits-amid-coronavirus-quarantines-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20days%20at%20home%20in%20pajamas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20go%20all%20in%20on%20the%20in-office%20hustle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwfhresearch.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWFHResearch_updates_June2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Survey%20of%20Working%20Arrangements%20and%20Attitudes%2C%20a%20monthly%20survey%20that%20has%20been%20running%20since%20May%202020%2C%20found%20that%20workers%20aged%2050-64%2C%20which%20spans%20older%20Gen%20X%20and%20younger%20boomers%2C%20are%20fully%20on-site%20the%20most%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20also%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdream-job-in-office-work-full-time-flexibility-benefits-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20full%20time.%20The%20survey%20examined%20where%20workers%20of%20different%20ages%20clocked%20in%20from%20February%20through%20May%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20contrasts%20with%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20younger%20millennials%2C%20who%20are%20the%20least%20likely%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-from-home-remote-work-increased-layoff-risk-job-market-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efully%20on-site%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20hybrid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fv3vZ2%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Working%20arrangements%20by%20age%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22259%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20data%2C%20which%20measured%20over%2013%2C200%20workers%2C%20those%20aged%2050-64%20were%20fully%20on-site%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20time%2C%20over%2011%20percentage%20points%20more%20than%20those%2020-29.%20Meanwhile%2C%20those%2020-29%20were%20most%20likely%20of%20any%20age%20demographic%20to%20work%20hybrid%20at%20nearly%20a%20third%2C%20almost%20double%20the%20rate%20of%20those%2050-64.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20those%2050-64%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20work%20fully%20remotely%2C%20while%20those%2020-29%20were%20least%20likely.%20The%20authors%20defined%20a%20full%20workday%20as%20six%20or%20more%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20about%2027%25%20of%20all%20paid%20days%20in%20May%202024%20were%20worked%20remotely%2C%20down%20slightly%20from%20earlier%20this%20year.%20Among%20employees%20able%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%20nearly%2038%25%20have%20zero%20work-from-home%20days%2C%20while%20those%20in%20the%20finance%20and%20information%20sectors%20are%20likelier%20to%20have%20two%20to%20three%20remote%20days.%20Employees%20able%20to%20work%20from%20home%20predict%20that%20a%20year%20from%20now%2C%20their%20employer%20plans%20for%20them%20to%20work%202.2%20days%20each%20week%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20comes%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-americans-super-commuting-75-miles-work-wfh-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupercommuting%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20workers%20traveling%20over%2075%20miles%20to%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20according%20to%20research%20by%20Stanford%20University%20economists%20Nick%20Bloom%20and%20Alex%20Finan.%20Supercommuting%20increased%20by%2032%25%20post-pandemic%2C%20while%20the%20share%20of%20commuters%20over%2040%20miles%20across%20the%20country's%2010%20largest%20cities%20also%20saw%20a%20large%20uptick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJose%20Maria%20Barrero%2C%20one%20of%20the%20survey's%20lead%20researchers%20and%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20Instituto%20Tecnol%C3%B3gico%20Aut%C3%B3nomo%20de%20M%C3%A9xico%20(ITAM)%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20believes%20two%20effects%20are%20driving%20the%20%26quot%3Bpolarization%26quot%3B%20among%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20one%20hand%2C%20those%20older%20workers%20need%20less%20mentoring%20and%20networking%20than%20younger%20ones.%20That%20means%20they%20can%20afford%20to%20be%20fully%20remote%20and%20might%20feel%20really%20comfortable%20doing%20things%20on%20their%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20Barrero%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20these%20folks%20have%20decades%20of%20experience%20and%20habit%20coming%20into%20the%20office.%20So%20that%20muscle%20memory%20might%20push%20them%20to%20come%20in%20more%20often%20than%20younger%20workers%20who%20embrace%20hybrid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20many%20older%20workers%20BI%20has%20spoken%20to%20are%20divided%20on%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20be%20in-office%20or%20at%20home%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20they're%20willing%20to%20leave%20roles%20that%20don't%20cater%20to%20their%20preferences.%20Dennis%20C.%2C%20a%2065-year-old%2C%20quit%20a%20six-figure%20job%20when%20his%20managers%20wanted%20him%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20said%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20have%20to%20come%20back%2C%20I%20sent%20them%20an%20email%20saying%20I'm%20retiring%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-return-to-office-baby-boomer-never-wants-go-back-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20took%20a%20slight%20pay%20cut%20to%20move%20into%20a%20fully%20remote%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%2062-year-old%20Charles%20Bond%20decided%20to%20retire%20early%20rather%20than%20work%20remotely.%20He%20said%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20bring%20his%20work%20home%20with%20him%2C%20and%20he%20liked%20being%20around%20others%20on%20his%20team%3B%20they're%20still%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20be%20around%20people.%20I%20enjoyed%20my%20team.%20I%20worked%20there%2027%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Bond%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-boomer-who-retired-rather-than-work-remotely-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20people%20there%20that%20had%20worked%20there%20just%20as%20long%20as%20me%2C%20if%20not%20longer.%20They%20were%20like%20a%20family.%20They%20were%20like%20my%20second%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20strongly%20prefer%20in-office%20or%20remote%20work%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%