AI%2C%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Oracle%2C%20Adobe%2C%20Meta%20%E2%80%94%20are%20dominated%20not%20by%20people%20who%20know%20how%20to%20build%20but%20by%20MBAs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsundar-pichai-google-alphabet-ceo-career-life%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagement%20consultants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20pencil%20pushers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20can%20save%20these%20companies%20is%20returning%20the%20tech%20industry%20to%20the%20people%20who%20actually%20build%20tech%20to%20solve%20problems%2C%20creating%20sustainable%2C%20meaningful%20markets%20based%20on%20fulfilling%20customer%20needs%20rather%20than%20increasingly%20complex%20growth%20machines%20that%20make%20customers'%20lives%20worse%20for%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDevelopers%20build%20it%2C%20managers%20tear%20it%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuilders%20dominated%20Silicon%20Valley's%20early%20years.%20Companies%20like%20Apple%20and%20Hewlett%20Packard%20were%20literally%20built%20in%20garages%2C%20as%20was%20Adobe%2C%20which%20was%20started%20by%20two%20computer%20scientists%20who%20left%20Xerox%20and%20developed%20PostScript%2C%20a%20pioneering%20language%20specifically%20built%20for%20printers.%20Both%20HP%20and%20Adobe%20now%20have%20CEOs%20with%20MBAs%2C%20and%20both%20companies%20have%20focused%20on%20creating%20shareholder%20value%20over%20meaningful%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20this%20tradition%20of%20growth%20through%20development%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20hack%20growth%20by%20subtly%20changing%20how%20information%20is%20presented%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20in%20notifications%20or%20in%20the%20content%20feed%20%E2%80%94%20to%20make%20users%20do%20things%20or%20spend%20more%20time%20on%20a%20platform.%20Instagram's%20founders%2C%20Kevin%20Systrom%20and%20Mike%20Krieger%2C%20both%20programmers%2C%20were%20promised%20autonomy%20when%20Facebook%20acquired%20the%20company%2C%20but%20in%20May%202018%20they%20found%20themselves%20ruled%20by%20a%20new%20master%3A%20Adam%20Mosseri%2C%20a%20former%20vice%20president%20of%20Facebook%20News%20Feed%2C%20who%20started%20his%20career%20as%20a%20designer%20and%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20time%20as%20a%20project%20manager.%20Systrom%20and%20Krieger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-cofounders-kevin-systrom-mike-krieger-leave-facebook-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclashed%20with%20Mosseri%20and%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20Facebook's%20encroaching%20on%20Instagram's%20independence%2C%20causing%20them%20to%20leave%20by%20September%202018.%20Since%20then%2C%20Instagram%20has%20gradually%20worsened%2C%20becoming%20more%20aggressively%20algorithmic%20and%20forcing%20users%20to%20see%20an%20endless%20flow%20of%20suggested%20videos%2C%20to%20the%20point%20where%20Kylie%20Jenner%20and%20Kim%20Kardashian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkylie-jenner-kim-kardashian-instagram-stop-trying-to-be-tiktok-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegged%20Mosseri%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20trying%20to%20be%20TikTok.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mosseri%20is%20not%20a%20technologist%20or%20a%20developer%2C%20and%20the%20mindset%20of%20a%20person%20who%20can't%20build%20things%20but%20wants%20to%20make%20a%20company%20money%20is%20always%20going%20to%20be%20to%20change%20the%20product%20to%20make%20it%20more%20profitable%20rather%20than%20more%20useful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pattern%20of%20replacing%20product-driven%20people%20with%20disconnected%20managers%20has%20been%20repeated%20across%20Silicon%20Valley.%20And%20even%20when%20nominally%20tech-steeped%20executives%20take%20the%20reins%20at%20major%20platforms%2C%20the%20management-consultant%2C%20growth-at-all-costs%20mindset%20still%20seems%20to%20seep%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Google%2C%20for%20one%20particularly%20gruesome%20example.%20Sundar%20Pichai%2C%20who%20became%20CEO%20in%202015%2C%20was%20previously%20a%20product%20manager%2C%20a%20powerful%20nontechnical%20role%20that%20makes%20calls%20about%20a%20product%20they%20have%20no%20hand%20in%20building.%20Under%20Pichai%2C%20the%20current%20leader%20of%20Google's%20core%20products%20is%20Prabhakar%20Raghavan.%20Nominally%2C%20Raghavan%20seems%20like%20the%20kind%20of%20person%20who%20would%20be%20committed%20to%20pushing%20products%20forward%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20a%20trained%20computer%20scientist%20who%20has%20authored%20academic%20papers%20in%20the%20field.%20But%20when%20he%20joined%20Google%2C%20he%20specifically%20did%20so%20as%20management%2C%20in%20what%20became%20one%20of%20the%20strangest%20moments%20of%20class%20treachery%20in%20tech-industry%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wheresyoured.at%2Fthe-men-who-killed-google%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%202019%2C%20Raghavan's%20ad%20and%20revenue%20teams%20began%20to%20clash%20with%20Google's%20main%20search%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20headed%20by%20Ben%20Gomes%2C%20a%20career%20technologist%20who%20helped%20build%20Google's%20search%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%20According%20to%20emails%20released%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice's%20recent%20antitrust%20case%20against%20Google%2C%20the%20search%20team%20was%20formally%20flagged%20because%20its%20revenue%20was%20down%20and%20there%20wasn't%20enough%20growth%20in%20%26quot%3Bqueries%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20in%20the%20volume%20of%20searches.%20Gomes%2C%20worried%20about%20Google's%20advertising%20arm%20influencing%20search%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20push%20to%20increase%20queries%20seemed%20to%20be%20driven%20by%20the%20advertising%20team's%20rapacious%20hunger%20for%20growth%20and%20that%20his%20search%20unit%20was%20getting%20%26quot%3Btoo%20close%20to%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%20Even%20after%20a%20round%20of%20changes%20resolved%20the%20search%20team's%20review%2C%20Raghavan%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bcore%20query%20softness%20continued%20without%20mitigation%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20layman's%20terms%2C%20people%20were%20still%20not%20searching%20on%20Google%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20represents%20the%20difference%20between%20a%20long-term%2C%20product-focused%20strategy%20and%20a%20short-term%2C%20cash-focused%20strategy.%20Having%20more%20people%20searching%20for%20more%20things%20is%20a%20good%20goal%2C%20but%20you%20also%20want%20to%20give%20people%20the%20answer%20for%20which%20they're%20searching.%20Having%20to%20rephrase%20a%20query%20five%20or%20six%20times%20to%20find%20an%20answer%20not%20only%20is%20frustrating%20but%20undermines%20the%20usefulness%20of%20the%20core%20product.%20Focusing%20solely%20on%20the%20number%20of%20searches%20runs%20contrary%20to%20the%20point%20of%20a%20search%20engine%2C%20as%20you're%20optimizing%20to%20make%20a%20user%20do%20%26quot%3Bmore%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20help%20them%20complete%20a%20query.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20eventually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-manipulates-search-results-report-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erolled%20out%20a%20more%20radical%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20how%20ads%20were%20shown%20in%20search%2C%20and%20just%20over%20a%20year%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-head-of-search-prabhakar-raghavan-ceo-sundar-pichai-alphabet-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaghavan%20was%20made%20head%20of%20search%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20Gomes%20relegated%20to%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20education.%20Now%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-documents-seo-leak-ranking-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Google%20Search%20is%20more%20profitable%20and%20worse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20elevating%20spammy%20content%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.khou.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Fcrime%2Fgoogle-search-scams%2F285-d896c74d-7497-4e5d-afae-0ff471c2bfee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutright%20scams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20problem%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-phishing-scams-automation-detection-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexacerbated%20by%20artificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fundamental%20difference%20is%20that%20builders%20are%20solutions-driven%20and%20managers%20are%20metrics-driven.%20The%20management-consultant%20mindset%20is%20founded%20not%20in%20understanding%20or%20respect%20for%20technology%20but%20in%20what%20can%20be%20extracted%20%3Cem%3Efrom%3C%2Fem%3E%20technology.%20Fundamentally%2C%20management-driven%20organizations%20are%20looking%20not%20to%20build%20things%20to%20fix%20consumers'%20pain%20points%20but%20to%20prioritize%20a%20nebulous%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Befficiency%26quot%3B%20that%20only%20makes%20products%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EVision%20and%20focus%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20have%20lost%20faith%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20in%20large%20part%20because%20it%20has%20failed%20to%20deliver%20on%20its%20core%20promise%3A%20making%20our%20lives%20better%20through%20technology.%20There%20was%20a%20time%20when%20Facebook%20and%20Google%20were%20respectable%2C%20profitable%20businesses%20that%20connected%20the%20world%3B%20chasing%20the%20dragon%20of%20perpetual%20growth%20has%20turned%20them%20against%20their%20users%2C%20making%20their%20products%20worse%20as%20a%20means%20of%20extracting%20more%20capital.%20Useful%20products%20are%20profitable%20products%2C%20but%20returning%20to%20utility%20will%20require%20both%20these%20companies%20and%20Wall%20Street%20to%20remember%20that%20growth%20is%20not%20eternal%20and%20that%20eventually%20users%20will%20be%20driven%20out%20when%20the%20products%20themselves%20turn%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20today's%20tech%20products%20feel%20built%20to%20sell%20a%20dream%20of%20the%20future%20rather%20than%20solve%20a%20customer's%20existing%20pains.%20The%20recent%20AI%20hype%20train%20seems%20to%20be%20totally%20divorced%20from%20reality%20%E2%80%94%20a%20survey%20from%20the%20Reuters%20Institute%20at%20Oxford%20University%20found%20that%20very%20few%20people%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-adoption-slow-google-bard-morgan-stanley-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eactually%20using%20generative%20AI%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20ChatGPT.%20Yet%20tech%20continues%20to%20try%20to%20force%20questionably%20useful%20ideas%20down%20our%20throats%20based%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20someday%20AI%20%3Cem%3Ecould%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20something%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20it's%20actually%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20should%20make%20you%20deeply%20suspicious%20of%20any%20promises%20made%20about%20the%20future%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20by%20the%20current%20crop%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20executives.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sam-altman-new-era-tech-villian-chatgpt-safety-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20spent%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20his%20career%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-hype-openai-silicon-valley-venture-capital-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E(badly)%20managing%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-glory-days-ending-problems-chatgpt-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20the%20technical%20power%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebehind%20OpenAI%2C%20nor%20has%20he%20been%20successful%20at%20anything%20other%20than%20making%20himself%20and%20his%20friends%20rich.%20So%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20top%20technical%20talent%20like%20the%20AI-governance%20researcher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-member-details-sam-altman-lied-allegation-ousted-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%