ol%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20estimates%20the%20likelihood%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20will%20change%20interest%20rates%20based%20on%20market%20predictions%2C%20there's%20a%2099.4%25%20chance%20rates%20will%20stay%20where%20they%20are%20as%20of%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20FOMC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-fed-pauses-increases-december-rate-cuts-powell-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforecast%20three%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20December%20projections%2C%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20has%20reiterated%20throughout%20the%20year%20that%20nothing%20is%20set%20in%20stone%2C%20and%20the%20nation's%20central%20bank%20is%20willing%20to%20hold%20out%20as%20long%20as%20necessary%20until%20it%20feels%20confident%20the%20economy%20has%20cooled%20down%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20quarter%20in%20the%20United%20States%20was%20notable%20for%20its%20lack%20of%20further%20progress%20on%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-staying-higher-for-longer-no-cuts-powell-inflation-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPowell%20said%20during%20a%20panel%20in%20Amsterdam%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20not%20expect%20this%20to%20be%20a%20smooth%20road%2C%20but%20these%20were%20higher%20than%20I%20think%20anybody%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20added.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20that%20has%20told%20us%20is%20that%20we'll%20need%20to%20be%20patient%20and%20let%20restrictive%20policy%20do%20its%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-food-energy-gas-prices-consumer-price-index-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConsumer%20Price%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%203.4%25%20for%20the%2012%20months%20ending%20April%2C%20which%20means%20it's%20still%20elevated.%20The%20next%20CPI%20report%20will%20be%20published%20on%20Wednesday%20morning.%20And%20the%20US%20labor%20market%20saw%20some%20strength%20in%20May%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-unemployment-rate-job-growth-looked-in-may-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20economy%20added%20272%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20month%2C%20which%20was%20way%20above%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investing.com%2Feconomic-calendar%2Fnonfarm-payrolls-227https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investing.com%2Feconomic-calendar%2Fnonfarm-payrolls-227%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomists'%20expectations.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20very%20interesting%20labor%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Julia%20Pollak%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20for%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20old%20normal.%20It's%20the%20new%20normal%20where%20employers%20are%20slower%20to%20fire%2C%20slower%20to%20hire%2C%20and%20workers%20are%20slower%20to%20switch%20jobs.%20That%20could%20be%20both%20a%20good%20thing%20and%20a%20bad%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20may%20be%20bad%2C%20partly%2C%20because%20it%20is%20driven%20in%20part%20by%20uncertainty%20and%20fear%20and%20high%20interest%20rates%20holding%20back%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollak%20added.%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%20it's%20good%20in%20other%20ways%20because%20some%20of%20it%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20jobs%20got%20better%20during%20the%20pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unemployment%20rate%20also%20ticked%20up%20to%204.0%25%20in%20May%3B%20the%20last%20time%20it%20was%20this%20rate%20was%20back%20in%20January%202022.%20Nick%20Bunker%2C%20the%20economic%20research%20director%20for%20North%20America%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20said%20May's%20rate%20is%20%26quot%3Bstill%20quite%20low%20historically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Joseph%20Briggs%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20while%20rate%20cuts%20%26quot%3Bhave%20been%20delayed%20somewhat%20by%20the%20stickier%20Q1%20inflation%2C%20we%20do%20think%20that%20we're%20still%20on%20track%20two%20this%20year%20starting%20in%20September.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-will-it-take-for-fed-to-cut-interest-rates-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutlined%20what%20it%20would%20take%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cut%20rates.%20During%20May's%20press%20conference%20following%20the%20FOMC's%20decision%20to%20hold%20rates%20steady%2C%20Powell%20said%20there%20are%20two%20paths%20that%20would%20give%20the%20Fed%20enough%20confidence%20to%20cut%20rates%3A%20more%20data%20to%20show%20inflation%20is%20getting%20closer%20to%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target%20or%20an%20%26quot%3Bunexpected%20weakening%20in%20the%20labor%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20did%20have%20a%20path%20where%20inflation%20proves%20more%20persistent%20than%20expected%2C%20and%20where%20the%20labor%20market%20remains%20strong%20but%20inflation%20is%20moving%20sideways%2C%20and%20we're%20not%20gaining%20greater%20confidence%2C%20that%20would%20be%20a%20case%20in%20which%20it%20could%20be%20appropriate%20to%20hold%20off%20on%20rate%20cuts%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Kelly%2C%20the%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20J.P.%20Morgan%20Asset%20Management%2C%20also%20told%20BI%20last%20week%20two%20rate%20cuts%20could%20happen%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20there'll%20be%20enough%20softness%20and%20coolness%20in%20the%20economy%20for%20them%20to%20begin%20to%20cut%20rates%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20I%20had%20to%20bet%2C%20I%20bet%20that%20we%20will%20get%20two%20rate%20cuts%2C%20one%20in%20September%20and%20one%20in%20December.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-fed-cut-interest-rates-elizabeth-warren-powell-rent-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epushing%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20give%20Americans%20some%20breathing%20room%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20European%20Central%20Bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fecb-lagarde-economy-interest-rates-cuts-inflation-growth-central-banks-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20rates%20earlier%20in%20June%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20five%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sens.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Jacky%20Rosen%2C%20and%20John%20Hickenlooper%20pointed%20to%20the%20ECB's%20actions%20as%20a%20sign%20that%20it's%20time%20for%20the%20US%20central%20bank%20to%20follow%20suit%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2024.06.10%2520Letter%2520to%2520Fed.%2520re%2520interest%2520rates.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Powell%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Fed's%20decision%20to%20keep%20interest%20rates%20highs%20continues%20to%20widen%20the%20rate%20gap%20between%20Europe%20and%20the%20U.S%2C%20as%20the%20lower%20interest%20rates%20could%20push%20the%20dollar%20higher%2C%20tightening%20financial%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20kept%20interest%20rates%20too%20high%20for%20too%20long%3A%20it%20is%20time%20to%20cut%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-when-will-fed-lower-rates-inflation-fomc-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718098201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66671b72e0790490181766ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-when-will-fed-lower-rates-inflation-fomc-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20booming%20jobs%2